
Overview of verb heap

The verb heap has 3 senses (first 2 from tagged texts)
                                           
1. (1) heap -- (bestow in large quantities; "He heaped him with work"; "She heaped scorn upon him")
2. (1) stack, pile, heap -- (arrange in stacks; "heap firewood around the fireplace"; "stack your books up on the shelves")
3. heap -- (fill to overflow; "heap the platter with potatoes")
